:: "You know Dad is having an affair right?" {"position":"2100,1700","size":"100,100"}
Cody: "What?" He laughs.

Delilah: "Yeah. It's true. I found a letter in his suitcase from some woman, probably a stripper."

Cody: "Dad wouldn't do something like that, quit making stuff up!"

Delilah: "She talked about how much she liked sleeping with him. They're probably together right now, Cody. That's why he isn't here..."

Cody: "No...Dad's on a business trip..."

Delilah: "Yeah! BUSINESS trip. That's a good one. Mom knows about it too. She's divorcing him soon and then you won't have a family anymore while I'm at college."

Cody: He looks at his feet and turns red, like he's about to start crying. Instead, something wells up in him and then dissipates in a long breath. "Oh," he says plainly. 

Delilah: "Oh?"

Cody: "Yeah. Oh. I guess I sort of knew already. Now that you point it out, it does make a lot of sense. I just didn't think it was possible. I think I need to go for a walk."

Delilah looks into his eyes to find what little life is in there slowly dimish into nothing. He didn't just lose his innocence, she ripped it out of him. 

Delilah: "Uh, Cody, the flower?"

Cody: "Oh, that. Yeah, it's in my room. Feel free to take it. I...don't think I'll need it anymore."

He leaves out the frontdoor into the night. Delilah doesn't stop him, instead going up the stairs to his bedroom to find the glowing flower sitting on his bed. As she takes it, she finds her memory expanding once again. 

Looking out the window, she sees Julian's body on the rocks by the lake. 

The End.
