:: Climb the tree {"position":"1500,900","size":"100,100"}
Something inside Delilah compels her to get that glowing flower. The way Julian mentioned gathering them before he ended up here and the way she suddenly was able to travel backwards by getting the first one, she felt that if she got another that maybe she'd get an answer as to why this was happening.

She used to climb trees all the time as a kid. Her dad would hoist her up and she'd cling to a branch like a koala. She thinks of this while planting her foot onto a knot on the side of its trunk. Higher and higher she reaches, farther and farther the ground becomes.

She inches her way across the tree's feeble branch and reaches for the flower. Once its in her hand she immediately feels different. Something eminates from the pedals of the flower into her mind. She's able to remember things in other ways and somehow remember things that would have been.

As soon as she feels this, the branch cracks under her and the ground throws itself at her. Her neck slams against the rocks and audibly snaps. She lays there facing Julian, staring into his eyes. As the light in her fades she notices how many colors can be seen in his irises. 

The End.

